predictions.rationale: The student consistently explains why slope corresponds to step changes, transfers the rise/run idea to new points and intercepts, and self-corrects/validates reasoning (e.g., sign placement and scaling steps) with minimal prompting.

The student can follow and apply factoring with sign checks to new examples and shows some self-correction, but their explanations stay procedural and they struggle to generalize when coefficients change (e.g., 2x^2) and with fractions.

The student consistently links equations to physical mechanisms, transfers ideas across topics (equipartition→heat capacities→adiabats→entropy→real-gas/JT), and independently proposes correct approximations and an inversion-temperature result.
